WEBVTT

00:10.662 --> 00:12.099
[exhales]

00:15.841 --> 00:17.365
Hi, Paula.

00:17.539 --> 00:18.235
Oh, my God.

00:19.541 --> 00:20.846
♪

00:22.805 --> 00:24.241
[gunshot]

00:24.415 --> 00:27.810
♪ When an irresistible force ♪

00:27.984 --> 00:30.769
♪ Such as you ♪

00:30.943 --> 00:34.904
♪ Meets an old
immovable object ♪

00:35.078 --> 00:37.124
♪ Like me... ♪

00:37.298 --> 00:39.300
[panting]:Okay.

00:39.474 --> 00:44.261
Um, seriously, where
do I drop you off?

00:44.435 --> 00:46.524
They're gonna check out
every place I've ever been

00:46.698 --> 00:49.092
and talk to anyone
who knows me.

00:49.266 --> 00:50.746
I'm staying with you
for a little bit.

00:50.920 --> 00:53.792
What? No, I'll pay for a hotel.

00:53.923 --> 00:54.924
A hotel?

00:55.098 --> 00:57.840
I'll get recognized.

00:58.014 --> 00:59.581
It's just gonna take a minute

00:59.755 --> 01:00.408
for my people figure
out something.

01:00.582 --> 01:01.931
It's fine.

01:04.673 --> 01:06.805
♪ Something's got to give,
something's got to give ♪

01:06.979 --> 01:10.374
♪ Something's got to give. ♪

01:15.597 --> 01:18.078
It's not very big.

01:18.252 --> 01:19.818
I just have it
when I work late

01:19.992 --> 01:20.950
and I don't want
to leave the city.

01:25.476 --> 01:27.043
Nice view.

01:31.134 --> 01:33.571
So...

01:33.745 --> 01:36.226
how long do you think
you're gonna need to stay here?

01:36.400 --> 01:39.011
Until I get in
touch with my boss.

01:39.186 --> 01:42.189
Hopefully, he'll have
a place for me soon.

01:46.715 --> 01:48.847
So I'll probablywant you

01:49.021 --> 01:51.850
to drop some things
off periodically.

01:52.024 --> 01:55.767
Clothes, groceries,
a phone, you know.

01:55.941 --> 02:00.381
Oh, and my guy Trevor,

02:00.555 --> 02:02.165
he'll stop by
and bring me dinner and stuff.

02:03.688 --> 02:05.690
Okay.

02:11.131 --> 02:12.480
So, you can go.

02:21.010 --> 02:23.099
♪

02:29.975 --> 02:31.977
LESLEY:
Oh, my God.

02:32.108 --> 02:33.849
What are you doing here?

02:34.023 --> 02:35.372
Me? What are you...

02:35.546 --> 02:37.113
Murphy, I can't
do this right now.

02:37.287 --> 02:39.071
I can't hear your apology.
Just get out of my face.

02:39.246 --> 02:41.117
I'm not here to apologize.
I-I'm trying to find Paula.

02:41.248 --> 02:42.640
What the hell
is going on?

02:42.814 --> 02:45.208
It's my apartment,Murphy.

02:45.339 --> 02:46.818
I made that stupid deal
to save Felix,

02:46.992 --> 02:48.385
and I couldn't find a legal way
to get her out.

02:48.559 --> 02:49.995
And then she was gonna kill me,
and here I am.

02:52.520 --> 02:54.609
Oh.

02:54.783 --> 02:56.567
Well, I-I really need
to talk to her.

02:56.698 --> 02:58.265
Why?

03:00.049 --> 03:02.356
Well, I just do.

03:08.100 --> 03:10.190
You're not wearing
that ankle monitor.

03:12.192 --> 03:13.541
That bizarre mistrial...

03:15.238 --> 03:16.370
You got a deal, didn't you?

03:18.807 --> 03:21.244
So, what? Deliver Paula
in return for your freedom?

03:21.375 --> 03:22.941
Oh, my God.Please let me talk to her.

03:23.072 --> 03:24.465
Listen to me.Please?

03:24.639 --> 03:26.162
Do not tell the cops
about this, okay?

03:26.336 --> 03:28.164
Do not tell the cops about this.
I will go to jail

03:28.295 --> 03:29.948
if she doesn't kill me first.

03:30.122 --> 03:32.037
I know you don't care
about what happens to me,

03:32.168 --> 03:35.215
but I do, okay? So please.

03:35.389 --> 03:37.304
[whispering]:
Just go.

03:40.829 --> 03:43.745
Go. Go.

03:50.273 --> 03:51.535
Who was that?

03:51.709 --> 03:54.756
Um, just a package.

03:54.930 --> 03:55.626
Where is it?

03:55.800 --> 03:57.106
What?

03:57.280 --> 03:58.716
The package.

03:58.890 --> 04:01.676
Oh, it was for my neighbor.

04:01.850 --> 04:03.286
He has me sign for him
when he's not home.

04:04.766 --> 04:06.115
Hmm.

04:12.469 --> 04:13.992
See?

04:19.346 --> 04:20.347
[exhales]

04:22.871 --> 04:25.613
Where is he? He's
never this late.

04:25.787 --> 04:27.005
I'm starving.

04:27.136 --> 04:29.443
I don't know.[sighs]

04:29.573 --> 04:31.053
I can grab you
some food if you want.

04:31.227 --> 04:33.098
You can order me something.

04:34.361 --> 04:35.971
What do you want?

04:36.145 --> 04:38.800
A burrito's fine.

04:38.974 --> 04:41.803
I also need you to stay with
me tonight. Maybe longer.

04:41.977 --> 04:43.761
I'm sorry?

04:43.935 --> 04:45.981
Something's up.What?

04:46.155 --> 04:48.679
My boss doesn't like his
people drawing attention.

04:48.810 --> 04:50.507
[chuckles]

04:50.681 --> 04:52.074
Which I clearly did.

04:54.816 --> 04:56.296
He hasn't answered any of
my texts since I've been here,

04:56.470 --> 04:58.515
and now Trevor isn't, either.

05:00.996 --> 05:02.345
I don't think I understand.

05:04.173 --> 05:05.043
He's edging me out.Who is?

05:05.174 --> 05:06.436
My boss.

05:08.960 --> 05:10.919
I'm not-- I-I mean...

05:11.049 --> 05:12.486
I don't think
I'm equipped to protect you.

05:12.616 --> 05:15.271
Oh, I'm not asking you
to protect me, babe.

05:15.445 --> 05:18.361
I just need you to scream first
so that I have time to escape.

05:20.058 --> 05:21.756
[TV playing indistinctly]

05:25.150 --> 05:26.369
Um, my phone's about to die.

05:26.543 --> 05:28.632
I have to go to my car
to get the charger.

05:28.806 --> 05:30.504
Charger?

05:30.634 --> 05:33.985
I'm at three percent.

05:34.159 --> 05:35.465
I need a charger
and yours doesn't work.

05:36.901 --> 05:39.121
Mm-hmm. Hurry.

05:41.253 --> 05:42.298
ANCHOR:
...be sure to call
the anonymous tip line

05:42.429 --> 05:44.648
or your local police department

05:44.822 --> 05:46.084
if they come across
any information at all

05:46.258 --> 05:47.825
that you believe
could lead to the arrest...

05:47.999 --> 05:49.174
[exhales]

05:51.525 --> 05:53.309
I can't believe
you told her.

05:53.483 --> 05:55.050
I didn't tell her,
she figured it out.

05:55.224 --> 05:57.705
And yes, shockingly fast.

05:57.879 --> 05:59.620
Let's just go.

05:59.750 --> 06:02.274
No. We have to convince
her to work with us.

06:02.449 --> 06:04.233
It's literally
our only option right now.

06:04.407 --> 06:05.452
[door closes]

06:07.236 --> 06:09.194
Oh, thank God.You need to leave.

06:09.369 --> 06:10.674
Just hear us out
for a second?

06:10.848 --> 06:11.893
No.

06:12.067 --> 06:13.677
We can help you, Lesley.

06:13.851 --> 06:16.463
Help me? You have
ruined my life

06:16.637 --> 06:18.813
on a level
I can't fully comprehend.

06:18.987 --> 06:22.120
You have destroyed my brother,
my relationship, everything.

06:22.294 --> 06:23.687
And now you're gonna
get me killed, so just move.

06:23.861 --> 06:26.429
Geez... Ow!

06:26.603 --> 06:28.736
Oh, my God.You okay?

06:28.910 --> 06:32.566
MURPHY: I guess.Look, look, look, look,
look, look, look.

06:32.740 --> 06:35.090
I get that you have
issues with Murphy.

06:35.264 --> 06:37.832
I don't blame you,
but you do need help.

06:38.006 --> 06:41.139
I'm good.You're not good.

06:41.313 --> 06:43.228
We can try to bring you in
on her deal.

06:43.359 --> 06:44.882
[scoffs]Your other option

06:45.056 --> 06:48.364
is we go to the cops
and tell them where Paula is,

06:48.538 --> 06:51.454
and then you go to jail
for, like, forever.

06:51.628 --> 06:53.630
Yeah, which I'm sure you'd love,

06:53.804 --> 06:55.371
so you and Max can live
happily ever after.

06:55.545 --> 06:58.113
We're not together. It's done.

06:58.287 --> 06:59.506
Sure.Fine, don't believe me.

06:59.680 --> 07:02.509
I don't.Okay.Can we focus on the situation?

07:02.683 --> 07:05.294
You really want
Paula staying with you?

07:05.468 --> 07:06.643
Can't imagine
that was your idea.

07:06.817 --> 07:08.863
I can't.

07:09.037 --> 07:11.169
If we go to the cops,
then I have to confess

07:11.343 --> 07:13.607
with absolutely
zero guarantee of immunity.

07:13.781 --> 07:15.086
We can get them
to agree beforehand.

07:15.260 --> 07:17.306
Cops lie. She lies. No.

07:17.480 --> 07:19.656
DARNELL:
Look, all we need
to do is find out

07:19.830 --> 07:22.137
who Paula's boss is,
whoever's in charge of Bolt,

07:22.311 --> 07:24.313
then everyone's good.

07:24.487 --> 07:25.967
You guys are good. What I need
is her out of my apartment.

07:26.097 --> 07:27.882
Which will happen.

07:28.056 --> 07:29.840
Okay? We turn in Paula's boss,

07:29.971 --> 07:32.103
they go down, Paula will flee.

07:32.277 --> 07:34.497
No one ever has
to know she was here.

07:35.759 --> 07:36.978
Trust me.

07:39.720 --> 07:41.373
Has she mentioned anything
about who she's working for?

07:41.548 --> 07:44.333
All she said is that her boss
isn't texting her back.

07:44.507 --> 07:46.509
Okay, so get
her phone.

07:46.683 --> 07:48.903
Get her phone
and we can get the contact.

07:49.077 --> 07:49.904
It's not that easy.
She literally showers

07:50.078 --> 07:51.862
with that thing.

07:51.993 --> 07:53.560
Can you get it
while she's sleeping?

07:53.734 --> 07:55.605
I don't know, Murphy. I don't...

07:55.779 --> 07:57.172
I don't know what to do.
I'm honestly too terrified

07:57.346 --> 07:59.000
to even go back up there.

07:59.174 --> 08:01.002
She thinks her boss wants her
dead, and she wants to use me

08:01.176 --> 08:02.960
as, like, a human
shield or something.

08:03.091 --> 08:04.701
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Why does she
think her boss wants her dead?

08:04.875 --> 08:06.834
Because her face is
plastered all over the news

08:07.008 --> 08:08.531
and apparently he doesn't
like any attention,

08:08.662 --> 08:10.228
now this dude Trevor
isn't responding

08:10.402 --> 08:11.360
and she thinks that means
that they're "edging her out."

08:15.886 --> 08:17.148
So that's why she thinks
someone is after her?

08:17.322 --> 08:20.891
Because this Trevor guy
isn't texting her back?

08:21.065 --> 08:21.936
Yeah.

08:24.721 --> 08:25.940
Don't.

08:26.114 --> 08:27.028
Come on.
Don't what?

08:27.158 --> 08:28.595
Nothing.Don't what?

08:28.769 --> 08:29.770
[sighs]Don't what?

08:29.944 --> 08:31.032
Trevor's dead.

08:33.034 --> 08:34.601
Great.

08:34.775 --> 08:35.950
What else you want me to do?

08:36.124 --> 08:36.994
Did you guys...No, of course not.

08:37.168 --> 08:38.518
We didn't
do anything,

08:38.692 --> 08:40.911
there was
a little accident, um...

08:41.042 --> 08:44.959
Trevor... he slipped.

08:45.133 --> 08:46.917
[exhales]And he fell and he...

08:47.048 --> 08:49.398
and he, and he's no longer
with us.

08:49.572 --> 08:51.269
You can't say anything

08:51.443 --> 08:52.314
because we obviously
have leverage on you.

08:53.707 --> 08:55.186
My point is

08:55.360 --> 08:58.494
that Paula's paranoia
is based on nothing.

08:58.668 --> 09:00.714
[sighs]Okay?
No one is coming after her.

09:00.888 --> 09:02.803
Which means you're safe
to go back up there

09:02.977 --> 09:04.761
and get her phone
while she's sleeping.

09:06.371 --> 09:08.460
Just write down
the number of the boss.

09:08.635 --> 09:10.071
We'll take care of the rest.

09:12.029 --> 09:13.944
Please, Lesley.

09:16.860 --> 09:18.253
Okay.

09:18.427 --> 09:19.167
Cool.
MURPHY:Yeah.

09:19.341 --> 09:21.256
Thanks.

09:21.430 --> 09:22.866
We'll, uh, call you
first thing.

09:35.357 --> 09:36.663
Hey.

09:40.014 --> 09:40.710
What are you doing here?

09:42.059 --> 09:43.974
Your mom called me.

09:45.323 --> 09:48.326
Oh, my God.
[exhales]

09:48.457 --> 09:50.764
What is going on?

09:50.938 --> 09:51.939
Nothing.

09:58.032 --> 09:59.163
Dude.

09:59.337 --> 10:00.991
Look.
[sighs]

10:01.122 --> 10:03.080
I'm not an idiot.

10:03.254 --> 10:04.647
I know you're back
doing what we used to.

10:04.778 --> 10:08.651
No, you don't know
anything, Max, okay?

10:08.782 --> 10:11.132
You arean
idiot. Just go.

10:11.306 --> 10:12.699
What is going on?

10:12.873 --> 10:15.266
Okay, this is
borderline stalking.

10:15.440 --> 10:18.922
I literally can't
not be with you.

10:19.096 --> 10:21.229
Okay? I-I had an out.

10:21.359 --> 10:23.666
Like, an actual job, maybe even
a life, and I didn't want it.

10:29.454 --> 10:31.065
I just love you
more than anything.

10:33.720 --> 10:34.721
[exhales]

10:40.596 --> 10:43.164
Murph.I don't know what to say.

10:46.341 --> 10:47.777
Sorry. That sucks for you.

10:51.128 --> 10:52.303
[soft chuckle]

10:52.477 --> 10:54.175
Whatever.

10:54.349 --> 10:55.829
Keep pushing me away.

10:59.049 --> 11:00.790
[door closes]

11:19.113 --> 11:20.854
♪

11:29.689 --> 11:31.429
[exhales]

11:57.542 --> 11:59.283
♪

12:01.024 --> 12:02.983
LESLEY:
I couldn't get it.

12:03.113 --> 12:04.027
She sleeps with that thing
inches from her head.

12:04.201 --> 12:05.986
There was no way.

12:06.116 --> 12:06.595
Well, you know, you
probably could've gotten it

12:06.769 --> 12:08.684
if you tiptoed.

12:08.858 --> 12:11.252
Instead of that, you
know, lumber of yours.

12:11.426 --> 12:13.123
What? I don't lumber.Yes, you do.

12:13.297 --> 12:14.821
You walk with a
very heavy foot.
DARNELL:
Guys.

12:14.995 --> 12:17.171
Stop. Okay? We need
to figure out how

12:17.345 --> 12:18.781
we're gonna get that phone.I'm telling you,

12:18.955 --> 12:21.218
she doesn't let it
out of her sight.

12:21.349 --> 12:22.785
We're gonna have to pry it
out of her cold dead hands.

12:26.484 --> 12:27.921
You are not killing her.

12:28.095 --> 12:29.923
I'm not suggesting
that, you psycho.

12:30.097 --> 12:32.229
[Lesley exhales]We need to get her
in, like, a...

12:32.403 --> 12:34.362
like a death-like state.What?

12:34.536 --> 12:36.364
Like, drug her?

12:36.494 --> 12:39.062
Huh. Not a terrible plan.

12:39.236 --> 12:40.281
How is that not
a terrible plan?

12:40.455 --> 12:41.412
You have another one?

12:41.586 --> 12:43.414
That is how.

12:43.588 --> 12:45.155
Don't you have sleeping pills?

12:45.286 --> 12:46.809
Yeah, but I have no idea
what the balance is

12:46.940 --> 12:48.376
of giving her enough
that she passes out,

12:48.506 --> 12:50.160
but not so much
that it kills her.

12:50.291 --> 12:52.728
I'm not risking that
because I don't kill people.

12:52.859 --> 12:54.382
Well, la-de-da.

12:54.512 --> 12:55.731
Sleeping pills wouldn't
work anyway.

12:55.862 --> 12:57.472
If she woke up...[Lesley sighs]

12:57.646 --> 12:59.387
Some jackass
roofied me once.

12:59.561 --> 13:02.085
What?Yeah.

13:02.259 --> 13:05.045
It was fine. I mean, Jess--
she noticed and took me home,

13:05.219 --> 13:06.873
but I don't remember anything.

13:07.047 --> 13:08.788
And I was out
for, like, hours.

13:08.962 --> 13:11.268
I mean, I guess
roofies are designed

13:11.442 --> 13:13.444
for exactly
what we need--

13:13.618 --> 13:16.665
knock someone out fast and have
them not remember what happened.

13:16.839 --> 13:18.885
Right. So, we just need
to figure out

13:19.059 --> 13:20.016
how to get our hands on some.

13:24.281 --> 13:25.805
Why are you guys looking at me?

13:25.979 --> 13:27.676
I don't have roofies.

13:27.850 --> 13:29.634
Sorry. Excuse me for assuming

13:29.765 --> 13:31.680
that the former drug dealer
might know how to get drugs.

13:31.854 --> 13:34.030
Uh, you are also
a former drug dealer.

13:35.336 --> 13:37.077
That's fair.

13:37.207 --> 13:39.644
I actually might know how
we might be able to get them.

13:39.775 --> 13:41.995
Back when I was
a public defender,

13:42.169 --> 13:44.519
I helped this guy Jake get off
on date-rape charges.

13:44.693 --> 13:46.042
[scoffs]I love how you were bragging

13:46.216 --> 13:47.217
about not killing people.

13:47.348 --> 13:48.218
He didn't do it.

13:48.349 --> 13:49.785
[scoffs]Look.

13:49.916 --> 13:51.308
He didn't deserve
to go to jail

13:51.482 --> 13:52.788
because his friends
assaulted someone.

13:52.919 --> 13:53.876
Okay.

13:54.050 --> 13:56.487
Anyway,

13:56.661 --> 13:58.663
I know the bar
where they got them.

13:58.794 --> 14:00.317
Hopefully, this bartender
still works there,

14:00.491 --> 14:01.971
and maybe we can buy some
off of him.

14:02.145 --> 14:03.277
MURPHY: Weird thing
to hope for, but sure.

14:07.063 --> 14:09.109
[knocks on doorframe]

14:10.501 --> 14:12.112
[rock music plays quietly]

14:19.336 --> 14:20.642
Josh, hi. [laughs]

14:20.816 --> 14:21.904
Oh.Ooh, sorry.

14:22.078 --> 14:23.471
Sorry.
[laughs]

14:23.601 --> 14:25.690
Sorry. I was...
I was waving. I didn't...

14:25.821 --> 14:27.736
Anyway, I forgot. Sorry.It's okay. It's okay.

14:27.910 --> 14:28.955
Um...It happens.

14:29.129 --> 14:30.217
Annoyingly often
these days.

14:30.391 --> 14:32.393
Uh, please.

14:33.481 --> 14:35.439
Um, hi.

14:35.613 --> 14:36.745
Hi.

14:36.919 --> 14:38.616
Uh, what do you have here?

14:38.790 --> 14:41.750
Uh, it's just...
It's some stuff I compiled.

14:41.924 --> 14:43.970
May I?Yeah, please.

14:59.986 --> 15:01.335
Wow. This is...

15:01.509 --> 15:03.163
Insane? Crazy?

15:03.337 --> 15:05.034
Dead brother will do that
to you, I guess.No, no, no.

15:05.208 --> 15:07.297
Honestly, I was gonna say
"impressive."

15:07.428 --> 15:09.169
Really?Really.

15:09.343 --> 15:11.867
I, um... I guess
it's good to know

15:12.041 --> 15:13.825
that there's someone out there
who also wants

15:14.000 --> 15:15.610
to see Murphy Mason go down
as badly as me.

15:15.784 --> 15:17.655
Yeah, well, she's a horrible,
deranged murderer

15:17.829 --> 15:20.745
who will lie, cheat, or kill
to avoid going to therapy, so...

15:20.876 --> 15:24.314
Exactly my... Exactly.

15:24.445 --> 15:25.576
And when she stands trial
a second time,

15:25.750 --> 15:26.708
she'll be found guilty.

15:26.882 --> 15:28.884
I'll make sure of it.

15:29.058 --> 15:30.842
I'm just worried
she might flee in the meantime.

15:31.017 --> 15:33.541
So, if we can get her on moving
your brother's body, then...

15:33.671 --> 15:35.935
She'll go back to jail and
actually pay for what she did.

15:44.204 --> 15:46.467
I don't get it. We know that
Ben died at the Linsmore,

15:46.641 --> 15:47.859
and we know that Murphy
was there at the same time.

15:48.034 --> 15:49.339
Like, how is that not enough?

15:49.470 --> 15:51.167
Because there's no proof
that Ben was even there.

15:51.341 --> 15:53.169
They broke all
the security cameras.

15:53.343 --> 15:55.389
[indistinct chatter]

15:55.563 --> 15:56.520
Not in the storage room.

15:57.957 --> 15:59.480
Did Ben go in the storage room?

16:01.612 --> 16:03.223
No.

16:05.355 --> 16:06.313
Do you still have that footage?

16:06.487 --> 16:08.358
I do, yeah.

